I use windows 10 is the default DOS.
The cursor will use a position, probably because the cursor is not insert type, resulting in overflow.
UpdateProgress will wrap.
In Mac OS is normal. I hope updateProgress can be compatible with windows DOS.
Only need 3 to 4 can be compatible with windows DOS.
You can test the windows.

Test the code is official

``` php
    public function actionTest() {
        Console::startProgress(0, 10, 'Insert Database: ');
        for ($n = 1; $n <= 10; $n++) {
            Console::updateProgress($n, 10);
        }
        Console::endProgress();
    }
```

